/>
</picture></div></div><div
class="block-intro-text"><p>The Virgin Islands consist of St. Thomas, St. Croix, St. John, Water Island, and some uninhabited cays. It features the prime natural resources of clean beaches, clear seas, a mild climate, and a natural harbor. This territory has a <a
href="https://siteselection.com/issues/2021/nov/a-blueprint-for-prosperity-beyond-tourism.cfm">competitive business industry</a> that is mostly reliant on ocean-related sectors, such as tourism and trade.</p><p>A range of resources for entrepreneurs and tax incentives for eligible businesses make the U.S. Virgin Islands a great place to start a new business venture. With a vibrant tourism industry and a strong range of training programs, this U.S. territory is an attractive destination for small business startups.</p></div></div></div></div><div
