id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section1-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-an-employer-identification-number>Get an employer identification number.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-an-employer-identification-number-288x288-20200918.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Get an employer identification number."></div></div><p>Nearly all businesses will need to register for federal taxes by <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-apply-for-an-ein">applying for an employer identification number</a>.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section1-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=register-your-business-in-the-u-s-virgin-islands>Register your business in the U.S. Virgin Islands.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-register-your-business-in-the-virgin-islands-288x288-20210111.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Register your business in the U.S. Virgin Islands."></div></div><p>While sole proprietorships and general partnerships do not have to file formal business formation documents with the territory, they must register a trade name if they intend on operating under a fictitious business name.</p><p>All other business entities must be registered with the Office of the Lieutenant Governor Division of Corporations and Trademarks. This can be done online via Catalyst and can cost between $150.00 and $300.00.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p><a
href="https://www.corporationsandtrademarks.vi.gov/usvi-master/">Log in to Catalyst</a> or create an account to gain access to the online filing services.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Once you're logged in, click "Online Services" above your account dashboard and open the drop-down menu.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Click on "Form a New Business."</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>In the menu to the right, select the entity type you want to register.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Another menu will open to the right. Click on the relevant link to form or register your business entity.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Follow the prompts, complete the online forms, and upload the required documentation.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>After completing the electronic signature and reviewing your application, click "Submit."</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section1-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-necessary-permits-and-certifications>Obtain necessary permits and certifications.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-necessary-permits-and-certifications-288x288-20210112.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain necessary permits and certifications."></div></div><p>In order to obtain a business license, which every business operating in the U.S. Virgin Islands must have, you may need to have other permits, clearances, or board certifications in order to get your business license.</p><p>Depending on the type of business, you may need to submit a review by the Department of Health. Only certain professions must be certified by their respective board. Navigate to the Department of Licensing and Consumer Affairs <a
href="https://dlca.vi.gov/boardcertifications/">board certifications directory</a> to find out if you need a board certification for your profession.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section1-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=apply-for-a-u-s-virgin-islands-business-license>Apply for a U.S. Virgin Islands business license.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-a-virgin-islands-business-license-288x288-20210112.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Apply for a U.S. Virgin Islands business license."></div></div><p>Every business operating in the U.S. Virgin Islands must obtain a business license from the Department of Licensing and Consumer Affairs (DLCA). Ensure that you have all the necessary certifications, clearances, and permits before submitting your business license application.</p><p><strong>Required documentation:</strong></p><ul><li>Certificate of Trade Name/Partnership and Corporation Registration.</li><li><a
href="https://ltg.gov.vi/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Collections-Document-Request.pdf">Tax clearance letter</a>.*</li><li>Police records check.*</li><li>Review by the Department of Planning and Natural Resources for zoning compliance.*</li><li>Review by the Fire Service for fire code compliance.</li><li>Review by the Department of Health, depending on the type of license needed.</li><li>Board certification, depending on the type of business/profession.</li></ul><p>*Review will be conducted on the applicant's behalf by the DLCA Division of Licensing.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Navigate to the DLCA <a
href="https://dlca.vi.gov/">website</a> and log in or create an account by selecting the relevant button below "Apply For License" on the right side of the page.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Once you're logged in to your account, scroll to the bottom of the page and click "Apply for New License."</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Follow the prompts, complete the online forms, and submit your business license application.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section2" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>2.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=determine-your-tax-obligations>Determine your tax obligations.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section2-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=contact-the-bureau-of-internal-revenue>Contact the Bureau of Internal Revenue.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-contact-the-bureau-of-internal-revenue-288x288-20210112.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Contact the Bureau of Internal Revenue."></div></div><p>Contact the U.S. Virgin Islands Bureau of Internal Revenue (BIR) to determine your tax obligations and filing requirements, and register as a taxpayer.</p><p><strong>Contact details for the BIR’s St. Thomas office:</strong></p><p>6115 Estate Smith Bay Ste 225
St. Thomas, U.S. Virgin Islands 00802
Telephone: (340) 715-1040</p><p><strong>Contact details for the BIR’s St. John office:</strong></p><p>P. O. Box 8305
St. John, U.S. Virgin Islands 00831
Telephone: (340) 777-1446</p><p><strong>Contact details for the BIR’s St. Croix office:</strong></p><p>Leroy A. Quinn Government Finance Center
4008 Estate Diamond, Plot 7B
Christiansted, U.S. Virgin Islands 00820
Telephone: (340) 773-1040</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Visit the BIR <a
href="https://bir.vi.gov/">website</a> and download the tax structure booklet and tax calendar for additional guidance.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section2-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=pay-income-tax>Pay income tax.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-pay-income-tax-vi-288x288-20210115_2021-01-15-083939.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Pay income tax."></div></div><p>The income tax laws applicable in the U.S. are mirrored in the U.S. Virgin Islands. As a result of the mirrored taxing structure, the income tax provisions of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 issued by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) are, with certain limitations, generally applicable to the U.S. Virgin Islands.</p><p>This also allows taxpayers to use many of the IRS forms to file their taxes with BIR, including <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/f1120.pdf">Form 1120</a> to file corporate income tax returns.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section2-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=submit-withholding-tax-deposits>Submit withholding tax deposits.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-tax-withholding-vi-288x288-20210115_2021-01-15-083918.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Submit withholding tax deposits."></div></div><p>The procedures regarding the withholding and remittance of income taxes, Social Security Taxes (FICA), and Federal Unemployment Taxes (FUTA) in the U.S. Virgin Islands are the same as in the U.S. However, while income taxes withheld from wages are submitted to the BIR, FICA and FUTA are remitted to the IRS Center in Philadelphia, PA 19255.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section2-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=pay-excise-tax>Pay excise tax.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-pay-excise-tax-vi-288x288-20210115_2021-01-15-083904.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Pay excise tax."></div></div><p>If you manufacture or import goods, merchandise, or commodities for sale or other business purposes in the U.S. Virgin Islands, you will have to pay excise tax on these.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Registered taxpayers can file their excise tax returns online by visiting the <a
href="https://excise.bir.vi.gov/">Virgin Islands Bureau of Internal Revenue</a>.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Enter you email address and a password. Click "Register."</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>Follow the prompts to create your account and access the online services.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=hire-employees-and-comply-with-labor-laws>Hire employees and comply with labor laws.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=report-new-hires>Report new hires.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-report-new-hires-288x288-20210115.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Report new hires."></div></div><p>Submit a <a
href="chrome-extension://efaidnbmnnnibpcajpcglclefindmkaj/https://www.vidol.gov/wp-content/dol_forms/nhr2016.pdf">new hire reporting form</a> to the U.S. Virgin Islands Department of Labor within 20 days of the date of hire.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section3-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-mandatory-insurance>Obtain mandatory insurance.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-mandatory-insurance-288x288-20210115_2021-01-15-083801.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain mandatory insurance."></div></div><p>All employers in the U.S. Virgin Islands who employ one or more employees must obtain workers' compensation insurance.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section3-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=submit-quarterly-reports>Submit quarterly reports.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-submit-quarterly-reports-288x288-20210115.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Submit quarterly reports."></div></div><p>Employers must <a
href="chrome-extension://efaidnbmnnnibpcajpcglclefindmkaj/https://www.vidol.gov/wp-content/dol_forms/12.pdf">register</a> with the U.S. Virgin Islands Department of Labor Unemployment Insurance Division and submit quarterly wage and contribution reports. The necessary forms are mailed to employers well ahead of the due dates.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section3-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=display-workplace-posters>Display workplace posters.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-display-workplace-posters-vi-288x288-20210115.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Display workplace posters."></div></div><p>Federal and U.S. Virgin Islands law requires employers to display certain workplace posters. Contact the U.S. Virgin Islands Department of Labor and visit the <a
href="https://www.dol.gov/general/topics/posters">U.S. Department of Labor website</a> to obtain the mandatory posters.</p></div></div></div></div> <script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"HowTo","name":"How to Start a Business in the Virgin Islands","description":"<p>In the U.S. Virgin Islands, most businesses must be registered with the Lieutenant Governor\u2019s Office Division of Corporations and Trademarks. All businesses must obtain a business license and register with the local Bureau of Internal Revenue (BIR), as taxes must be paid to the BIR instead of the IRS.<\/p>\n","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-complete-800x800-20210111.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=250&dpr=2","height":"800","width":"800"},"estimatedCost":{"@type":"MonetaryAmount","currency":"USD","value":"150.00"},"totalTime":"P1M","step":[{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"1","name":"<p>Form your business.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Review formation options in the U.S. Virgin Islands.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>The U.S. Virgin Islands offer <a href=\"#virgin-islands-business-types\">seven ways of forming your business<\/a>, which we cover in detail below. Review these closely and pick the one that fits your business best.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands#how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section1-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-familiarize-yourself-with-the-key-business-structures-288x288-20200820_2023-09-15-072444_xekq.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Name your business.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Once you have decided on a business name, you must <a href=\"https:\/\/www.namesnack.com\/guides\/virgin-islands-business-search\">check its availability<\/a>. If