0200918.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"4","name":"<p>Register your business in the U.S. Virgin Islands.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>While sole proprietorships and general partnerships do not have to file formal business formation documents with the territory, they must register a trade name if they intend on operating under a fictitious business name.<\/p>\n<p>All other business entities must be registered with the Office of the Lieutenant Governor Division of Corporations and Trademarks. This can be done online via Catalyst and can cost between $150.00 and $300.00.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands#how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section1-step4","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-register-your-business-in-the-virgin-islands-288x288-20210111.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.corporationsandtrademarks.vi.gov\/usvi-master\/\">Log in to Catalyst<\/a> or create an account to gain access to the online filing services.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Once you're logged in, click \"Online Services\" above your account dashboard and open the drop-down menu.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Click on \"Form a New Business.\"<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>In the menu to the right, select the entity type you want to register.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Another menu will open to the right. Click on the relevant link to form or register your business entity.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Follow the prompts, complete the online forms, and upload the required documentation.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>After completing the electronic signature and reviewing your application, click \"Submit.\"<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"5","name":"<p>Obtain necessary permits and certifications.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>In order to obtain a business license, which every business operating in the U.S. Virgin Islands must have, you may need to have other permits, clearances, or board certifications in order to get your business license.<\/p>\n<p>Depending on the type of business, you may need to submit a review by the Department of Health. Only certain professions must be certified by their respective board. Navigate to the Department of Licensing and Consumer Affairs <a href=\"https:\/\/dlca.vi.gov\/boardcertifications\/\">board certifications directory<\/a> to find out if you need a board certification for your profession.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands#how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section1-step5","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-necessary-permits-and-certifications-288x288-20210112.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"6","name":"<p>Apply for a U.S. Virgin Islands business license.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Every business operating in the U.S. Virgin Islands must obtain a business license from the Department of Licensing and Consumer Affairs (DLCA). Ensure that you have all the necessary certifications, clearances, and permits before submitting your business license application.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Required documentation:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Certificate of Trade Name\/Partnership and Corporation Registration.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/ltg.gov.vi\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/Collections-Document-Request.pdf\">Tax clearance letter<\/a>.*<\/li>\n<li>Police records check.*<\/li>\n<li>Review by the Department of Planning and Natural Resources for zoning compliance.*<\/li>\n<li>Review by the Fire Service for fire code compliance.<\/li>\n<li>Review by the Department of Health, depending on the type of license needed.<\/li>\n<li>Board certification, depending on the type of business\/profession.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>*Review will be conducted on the applicant's behalf by the DLCA Division of Licensing.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands#how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section1-step6","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-a-virgin-islands-business-license-288x288-20210112.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Navigate to the DLCA <a href=\"https:\/\/dlca.vi.gov\/\">website<\/a> and log in or create an account by selecting the relevant button below \"Apply For License\" on the right side of the page.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Once you're logged in to your account, scroll to the bottom of the page and click \"Apply for New License.\"<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Follow the prompts, complete the online forms, and submit your business license application.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"2","name":"<p>Determine your tax obligations.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Contact the Bureau of Internal Revenue.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Contact the U.S. Virgin Islands Bureau of Internal Revenue (BIR) to determine your tax obligations and filing requirements, and register as a taxpayer.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Contact details for the BIR\u2019s St. Thomas office:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>6115 Estate Smith Bay Ste 225\nSt. Thomas, U.S. Virgin Islands 00802\nTelephone: (340) 715-1040<\/p>\n<p><strong>Contact details for the BIR\u2019s St. John office:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>P. O. Box 8305\nSt. John, U.S. Virgin Islands 00831\nTelephone: (340) 777-1446<\/p>\n<p><strong>Contact details for the BIR\u2019s St. Croix office:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Leroy A. Quinn Government Finance Center\n4008 Estate Diamond, Plot 7B\nChristiansted, U.S. Virgin Islands 00820\nTelephone: (340) 773-1040<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands#how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section2-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-contact-the-bureau-of-internal-revenue-288x288-20210112.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Visit the BIR <a href=\"https:\/\/bir.vi.gov\/\">website<\/a> and download the tax structure booklet and tax calendar for additional guidance.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Pay income tax.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>The income tax laws applicable in the U.S. are mirrored in the U.S. Virgin Islands. As a result of the mirrored taxing structure, the income tax provisions of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 issued by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) are, with certain limitations, generally applicable to the U.S. Virgin Islands.<\/p>\n<p>This also allows taxpayers to use many of the IRS forms to file their taxes with BIR, including <a href=\"https:\/\/www.irs.gov\/pub\/irs-pdf\/f1120.pdf\">Form 1120<\/a> to file corporate income tax returns.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands#how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section2-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-pay-income-tax-vi-288x288-20210115_2021-01-15-083939.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Submit withholding tax deposits.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>The procedures regarding the withholding and remittance of income taxes, Social Security Taxes (FICA), and Federal Unemployment Taxes (FUTA) in the U.S. Virgin Islands are the same as in the U.S. However, while income taxes withheld from wages are submitted to the BIR, FICA and FUTA are remitted to the IRS Center in Philadelphia, PA 19255.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands#how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section2-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-tax-withholding-vi-288x288-20210115_2021-01-15-083918.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"4","name":"<p>Pay excise tax.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>If you manufacture or import goods, merchandise, or commodities for sale or other business purposes in the U.S. Virgin Islands, you will have to pay excise tax on these.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands#how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands-section2-step4","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-pay-excise-tax-vi-288x288-20210115_2021-01-15-083904.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Registered taxpayers can file their excise tax returns online by visiting the <a href=\"https:\/\/excise.bir.vi.gov\/\">Virgin Islands Bureau of Internal Revenue<\/a>.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Enter you email address and a password. Click \"Register.\"<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Follow the prompts to create your account and access the online services.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"3","name":"<p>Hire employees and comply with labor laws.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Report new hires.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Submit a <a href=\"chrome-extension:\/\/efaidnbmnnnibpcajpcglclefindmkaj\/https:\/\/www.vidol.gov\/wp-content\/dol_forms\/nhr2016.pdf\">new hire reporting form<\/a> to the U.S. Virgin Islands Department of Labor within 20 days of the date of hire.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-business-in-the-virgin-islands#how-to-start-a-business-in-the-vir